WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.740
for God's word and a tremendous blessing

00:00:03.740 --> 00:00:05.460
to be able to have a Bible.

00:00:05.460 --> 00:00:07.179
This year on Wednesdays,

00:00:07.179 --> 00:00:09.539
we've been really dealing with this thought

00:00:09.539 --> 00:00:12.460
of having a desire to see God work,

00:00:12.460 --> 00:00:15.420
to see God do what only God can do.

00:00:15.420 --> 00:00:17.940
And we've understood as we've studied

00:00:17.940 --> 00:00:19.739
various portions of scripture

00:00:19.739 --> 00:00:22.379
on Wednesdays throughout 2026,

00:00:22.379 --> 00:00:24.500
we've understood the fact that

00:00:24.500 --> 00:00:27.440
we have a longing to see God work.

00:00:27.440 --> 00:00:30.819
The Psalmist said, it is time Lord for thee to work,

00:00:30.819 --> 00:00:33.119
for they have made void thy law.

00:00:33.119 --> 00:00:36.819
And we've said that we desire to see God work,

00:00:36.819 --> 00:00:40.840
to see God do again what only God can do.

00:00:40.840 --> 00:00:43.919
We've acknowledged the fact that God is able to work.

00:00:43.919 --> 00:00:46.880
And that's a blessing to know that

00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:48.919
we are longing for God to work,

00:00:48.919 --> 00:00:52.360
but he has the power, he has the ability.

00:00:52.360 --> 00:00:55.139
The Psalmist tells us that he's a very present help

00:00:55.139 --> 00:00:56.659
in the time of trouble.

00:00:56.659 --> 00:00:59.979
And I think about having a desire for someone

00:00:59.979 --> 00:01:03.700
or something to work and it doesn't work.

00:01:03.700 --> 00:01:05.319
I use the illustration this morning

00:01:05.319 --> 00:01:08.480
with the Wednesday morning crowd.

00:01:08.480 --> 00:01:12.559
We have a snowblower and the desire when it snows

00:01:12.559 --> 00:01:14.660
is that your snowblower works.

00:01:14.660 --> 00:01:17.139
And that just makes sense, amen.

00:01:17.139 --> 00:01:20.540
And sure enough, January, big snowstorm,

00:01:20.540 --> 00:01:24.139
all that snow comes in and I'm sitting in Hawaii

00:01:24.139 --> 00:01:26.720
with Holly visiting our daughter and grandkids

00:01:26.720 --> 00:01:29.559
and got out of town before all the snow came

00:01:29.559 --> 00:01:31.760
and Joseph said, this thing won't work

00:01:31.760 --> 00:01:34.139
and couldn't get the snowblower to work.

00:01:34.139 --> 00:01:36.360
And that was most disappointing.

00:01:36.360 --> 00:01:39.680
And I told Joseph, one thing I was confident of

00:01:39.680 --> 00:01:41.839
is that if he couldn't get it to work,

00:01:41.839 --> 00:01:43.720
that there was no hope that if I were here

00:01:43.720 --> 00:01:44.839
that I'd get it to work

00:01:44.839 --> 00:01:47.339
because he's much more mechanical than I am.

00:01:47.339 --> 00:01:48.959
And we just had nothing.

00:01:48.959 --> 00:01:50.440
And so that thing didn't work.

00:01:50.440 --> 00:01:54.459
We had a piece of machinery, but nothing going.

00:01:54.459 --> 00:01:57.839
And you think about that, that happens sometimes in life

00:01:57.839 --> 00:01:59.760
with things, even with people.

00:01:59.760 --> 00:02:01.300
We want somebody to help with something,

00:02:01.300 --> 00:02:03.720
they're not available, whatever it might be.

00:02:03.720 --> 00:02:05.680
But I want you to acknowledge this evening

00:02:05.680 --> 00:02:09.119
that God is always available and God has all power

00:02:09.119 --> 00:02:13.039
and he is a very present help in the time of trouble

00:02:13.039 --> 00:02:15.380
and he is able to work.

00:02:15.380 --> 00:02:18.600
We've also understood and it's one of those things

00:02:18.600 --> 00:02:20.320
that's important for us to look at.

00:02:21.160 --> 00:02:23.080
That's a little bit maybe something

00:02:23.080 --> 00:02:25.759
we don't wanna acknowledge or admit, but we must.

00:02:25.759 --> 00:02:29.559
And that is this, our doubt or our unbelief

00:02:29.559 --> 00:02:32.080
limits God from working.

00:02:32.080 --> 00:02:33.960
The Bible says in Psalm 78

00:02:33.960 --> 00:02:37.080
that they limited the Holy One of Israel.

00:02:37.080 --> 00:02:38.679
The Bible tells us in Matthew 13,

00:02:38.679 --> 00:02:40.279
as we've studied throughout this year,

00:02:40.279 --> 00:02:43.479
that he did not many mighty works there, why?

00:02:43.479 --> 00:02:45.919
Because of their unbelief.

00:02:45.919 --> 00:02:49.679
And so this week, as we've looked at numbers 13 and 14,

00:02:49.880 --> 00:02:52.000
last week we kind of started here.

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:54.839
And last week we talked about identifying doubt.

00:02:54.839 --> 00:02:58.119
How does doubt come into your life and into my life

00:02:58.119 --> 00:03:00.080
and how do we identify it?

00:03:00.080 --> 00:03:03.679
And if we don't identify it, then we can't deal with it.

00:03:03.679 --> 00:03:06.000
And we use the analogy and we'll continue

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:08.240
to use the analogy this evening.

00:03:08.240 --> 00:03:10.360
The analogy last week was of a garden

00:03:10.360 --> 00:03:13.199
and whether it's a vegetable garden, a flower garden,

00:03:13.199 --> 00:03:14.960
you plant that which you want,

00:03:14.960 --> 00:03:18.619
but you understand that weeds are probably going to pop up.

00:03:18.660 --> 00:03:22.300
And we said that the flower, the plant is like faith,

00:03:22.300 --> 00:03:24.419
but the weeds are like doubt.

00:03:24.419 --> 00:03:27.399
And you need to be able to identify the doubt

00:03:27.399 --> 00:03:28.779
so that you can get rid of it.

00:03:28.779 --> 00:03:31.899
You need to be able to identify the weeds

00:03:31.899 --> 00:03:36.419
so that you can move it, remove it from the garden.

00:03:36.419 --> 00:03:41.419
And if we do not identify it, then we cannot deal with it.

00:03:41.500 --> 00:03:43.860
But just because we identify it

00:03:43.860 --> 00:03:48.020
doesn't mean we will deal with it, right?

00:03:48.899 --> 00:03:50.779
And so this evening we're gonna talk

00:03:50.779 --> 00:03:52.979
about the consequences of doubt.

00:03:52.979 --> 00:03:55.940
What happens in your life and in my life

00:03:55.940 --> 00:03:59.660
when doubt, unbelief is present?

00:03:59.660 --> 00:04:02.360
Just like those weeds in the garden,

00:04:02.360 --> 00:04:04.779
if we do not deal with them,

00:04:04.779 --> 00:04:08.399
eventually what happens is the weeds take over.

00:04:08.399 --> 00:04:11.660
And you've seen gardens, you've seen flower beds

00:04:11.660 --> 00:04:14.580
where the weeds have just totally taken over

00:04:14.580 --> 00:04:17.940
and they'll choke out the things that you've planted,

00:04:17.980 --> 00:04:21.540
that you've desired to reap a harvest from.

00:04:21.540 --> 00:04:24.019
And so when we looked at this portion of scripture

00:04:24.019 --> 00:04:26.820
last week, we found at least three reasons

00:04:26.820 --> 00:04:30.220
that the people of God began to doubt what God said.

00:04:30.220 --> 00:04:33.820
They had unbelief and we were able to learn those things.

00:04:33.820 --> 00:04:37.779
But now as we begin to consider the consequences of doubt,

00:04:37.779 --> 00:04:40.619
I hope that it would help us to have

00:04:40.619 --> 00:04:42.859
just a greater concern in our lives

00:04:42.859 --> 00:04:47.299
to be able to identify and deal with that doubt.

00:04:47.299 --> 00:04:50.299
Let me say this, last week I said that doubt,

00:04:50.299 --> 00:04:53.899
unbelief is sin and it is, it's sin.

00:04:53.899 --> 00:04:58.899
We don't believe God, we doubt what God says, it's sin.

00:04:59.140 --> 00:05:01.980
And it's important that we acknowledge

00:05:01.980 --> 00:05:06.980
that doubt is not benign, it is not harmless.

00:05:07.019 --> 00:05:09.739
Doubt is not something that we just kind of think,

00:05:09.739 --> 00:05:13.420
oh, it can exist and it's not gonna really do anything bad.

00:05:13.420 --> 00:05:17.859
Doubt and unbelief needs to be rooted out

00:05:17.859 --> 00:05:19.899
of the life of a believer.

00:05:19.899 --> 00:05:23.459
We find that the Bible says that without faith,

00:05:23.459 --> 00:05:26.059
it is impossible to please him.

00:05:26.059 --> 00:05:28.579
For he that cometh to God must believe that he is

00:05:28.579 --> 00:05:32.079
and that he's a rewarder of them that diligently seek him.

00:05:32.079 --> 00:05:33.859
In Hebrews 11 and verse number six,

00:05:33.859 --> 00:05:36.660
throughout the scriptures, Old and New Testament,

00:05:36.660 --> 00:05:41.660
we read this truth that the just shall live by faith.

00:05:41.820 --> 00:05:44.980
And faith is believing God, taking God at his word.

00:05:44.980 --> 00:05:48.100
And so this evening as we consider some of the consequences

00:05:48.100 --> 00:05:50.739
of doubt, I hope that it would help us to have

00:05:50.739 --> 00:05:55.700
a greater desire to rid and root out doubt from our lives.

00:05:55.700 --> 00:05:57.380
Number one, I have five thoughts,

00:05:57.380 --> 00:06:00.299
they're not gonna be lengthy, but number one this evening,

00:06:00.299 --> 00:06:02.619
I want you to recognize that your doubt

00:06:02.619 --> 00:06:06.380
and my doubt will impact others.

00:06:06.380 --> 00:06:07.859
It will impact others.

00:06:07.859 --> 00:06:10.100
Let's look at the passage of scripture.

00:06:10.140 --> 00:06:12.940
In Numbers chapter 13, beginning in verse number one,

00:06:12.940 --> 00:06:16.459
the Bible says, and the Lord spake unto Moses saying,

00:06:16.459 --> 00:06:19.619
and here's the instructions that God gives to Moses,

00:06:19.619 --> 00:06:24.279
send thou men that they may search the land of Canaan,

00:06:24.279 --> 00:06:26.839
which I give unto the children of Israel.

00:06:26.839 --> 00:06:29.220
Notice of every tribe of their father,

00:06:29.220 --> 00:06:34.220
shall you send a man, everyone a ruler among them.

00:06:34.540 --> 00:06:38.179
It says in verse number four, and these were their names

00:06:38.179 --> 00:06:41.100
from verse four down through verse number 15,

00:06:41.100 --> 00:06:44.619
you read the names of those that are assigned the task.

00:06:44.619 --> 00:06:47.959
It says in verse 16, these are the names of the men

00:06:47.959 --> 00:06:50.980
which Moses sent to spy out the land.

00:06:50.980 --> 00:06:53.739
And so we find that verse number two says,

00:06:53.739 --> 00:06:58.540
of every tribe of their fathers, shall you send a man.

00:06:58.540 --> 00:07:01.540
That means there's 12 spies, all right?

00:07:01.540 --> 00:07:03.220
Now we sing the song with the kids,

00:07:03.220 --> 00:07:06.799
12 men went to spy on Canaan, 10 were bad and two were good.

00:07:06.799 --> 00:07:09.600
And so we think about that and we understand this evening

00:07:09.600 --> 00:07:12.399
that there's 12 spies.

00:07:12.399 --> 00:07:15.440
Now we know that Joshua and Caleb are the two good spies

00:07:15.440 --> 00:07:20.440
and so that leaves us with 10 men that are these evil spies

00:07:20.799 --> 00:07:22.640
that bring back this evil report.

00:07:22.640 --> 00:07:27.279
The Bible tells us in verse number 27, and they told him,

00:07:27.279 --> 00:07:31.279
that's the spies as they return, they tell Moses,

00:07:31.279 --> 00:07:33.239
they're bringing back the report.

00:07:33.239 --> 00:07:35.700
And remember in verse 27, we looked at it last week,

00:07:35.700 --> 00:07:38.980
they begin to tell about the land and what they saw,

00:07:38.980 --> 00:07:41.640
but they say this in verse 28, nevertheless,

00:07:41.640 --> 00:07:43.679
and it changes direction.

00:07:43.679 --> 00:07:45.940
They get their eyes off of what they're supposed

00:07:45.940 --> 00:07:47.899
to be looking at and considering,

00:07:47.899 --> 00:07:49.739
and they begin to look at the circumstances.

00:07:49.739 --> 00:07:52.160
They begin to get their eyes on the obstacles

00:07:52.160 --> 00:07:54.820
that they would face and they begin to talk about the fact

00:07:54.820 --> 00:07:57.779
that the cities are walled and very great,

00:07:57.779 --> 00:08:00.500
that the sons of Anak, the giants are there

00:08:00.500 --> 00:08:03.380
and they're overwhelmed with the obstacles

00:08:03.380 --> 00:08:06.420
and they conclude, according to verse number 31,

00:08:06.420 --> 00:08:09.899
we be not able to go up against the people

00:08:09.899 --> 00:08:12.519
for they are stronger than we.

00:08:12.519 --> 00:08:15.660
So Joshua and Caleb, Caleb here in chapter number 13

00:08:15.660 --> 00:08:17.859
in verse 30, he tries to steal the people.

00:08:17.859 --> 00:08:21.540
Joshua and Caleb are two good spies out of the 12,

00:08:21.540 --> 00:08:23.859
but I want you to consider with me this evening

00:08:23.859 --> 00:08:27.299
that your doubt and my doubt will impact others

00:08:27.299 --> 00:08:29.720
because as we notice this, as we look at these verses,

00:08:29.720 --> 00:08:32.719
there's 10 men, 10.

00:08:32.719 --> 00:08:33.960
That's not a big number.

00:08:35.200 --> 00:08:38.640
It's a small number, but begin reading in chapter 14

00:08:38.640 --> 00:08:41.119
in verse number one, the Bible says this,

00:08:41.119 --> 00:08:46.119
and all the congregation lifted up their voice

00:08:47.359 --> 00:08:50.039
and cried and the people wept that night.

00:08:50.039 --> 00:08:53.559
Notice again in verse two, and all the children of Israel

00:08:53.559 --> 00:08:56.559
murmured against Moses and against Aaron

00:08:56.559 --> 00:08:59.719
and the whole congregation said unto them,

00:08:59.719 --> 00:09:02.719
would God that we had died in the land of Egypt

00:09:02.719 --> 00:09:06.799
or would God we had died in this wilderness

00:09:06.799 --> 00:09:09.280
and wherefore hath the Lord brought us unto this land

00:09:09.280 --> 00:09:11.840
to fall by the sword that our wives and our children

00:09:11.840 --> 00:09:14.239
should be a prey were it not better for us

00:09:14.239 --> 00:09:15.640
to return into Egypt.

00:09:15.640 --> 00:09:17.640
Notice in verse number 10, it says,

00:09:17.640 --> 00:09:21.280
but all the congregation bade stone them with stones

00:09:21.280 --> 00:09:23.320
and the glory of the Lord appeared in the tabernacle

00:09:23.320 --> 00:09:26.320
of the congregation before all the children of Israel.

00:09:27.080 --> 00:09:29.520
So we notice that there's 10 men in chapter number 13,

00:09:29.520 --> 00:09:30.880
but when we come to chapter number 14,

00:09:30.880 --> 00:09:33.039
it says in all the congregation,

00:09:33.039 --> 00:09:35.640
it says that the whole congregation,

00:09:35.640 --> 00:09:39.320
all the children of Israel, it says all the congregation

00:09:39.320 --> 00:09:40.919
bade stone them with stones.

00:09:40.919 --> 00:09:42.440
We don't know, you can look in the beginning

00:09:42.440 --> 00:09:46.159
of Numbers chapter one, you can begin to see the numbers

00:09:46.159 --> 00:09:49.280
that are provided with regard to the various tribes.

00:09:49.280 --> 00:09:52.119
There's probably a couple million people

00:09:52.119 --> 00:09:55.599
that are influenced by 10, by 10.

00:09:56.320 --> 00:09:59.400
Your doubt and my doubt.

00:09:59.400 --> 00:10:02.660
influences and impacts others.

00:10:02.660 --> 00:10:04.700
You think about a generation that's following us.

00:10:04.700 --> 00:10:07.340
If parents don't have faith,

00:10:07.340 --> 00:10:09.700
if they don't believe that God is able,

00:10:09.700 --> 00:10:11.780
if church leaders don't have faith

00:10:11.780 --> 00:10:14.140
and believe that God is able,

00:10:14.140 --> 00:10:16.620
what's gonna happen to the others?

00:10:16.620 --> 00:10:18.820
What's gonna happen to the next generation?

00:10:19.940 --> 00:10:24.420
Our doubt, our unbelief, our lack of faith

00:10:24.420 --> 00:10:27.900
will impact others and we see it here

00:10:27.900 --> 00:10:32.140
in Numbers 13 and 14, very, very obvious to us.

00:10:32.140 --> 00:10:33.900
In Galatians 5 and verse number nine,

00:10:33.900 --> 00:10:37.660
the Bible says a little leaven leaveneth the whole lump.

00:10:37.660 --> 00:10:41.160
Just a little impacts the whole.

00:10:41.160 --> 00:10:43.020
And so we understand this evening

00:10:43.020 --> 00:10:44.620
the consequences of doubt.

00:10:44.620 --> 00:10:47.740
Sometimes we're led to think or we like to believe

00:10:47.740 --> 00:10:50.940
that we operate and function in some type of a bubble

00:10:50.940 --> 00:10:53.940
and all that we do and all that we are only affects us,

00:10:53.940 --> 00:10:55.280
but that's just not true.

00:10:56.280 --> 00:10:58.960
And our doubt will impact others

00:10:58.960 --> 00:11:03.720
and I'd rather that my faith impacts others, amen?

00:11:03.720 --> 00:11:06.520
That people see the faith of somebody

00:11:06.520 --> 00:11:09.600
that just believes God, that just trusts God

00:11:09.600 --> 00:11:13.440
and that will have an influence and an impact.

00:11:13.440 --> 00:11:16.480
But these 10 men, they influenced an entire congregation.

00:11:16.480 --> 00:11:17.920
Let me say this, number two,

00:11:17.920 --> 00:11:21.160
not only will our doubt and our unbelief impact others,

00:11:21.160 --> 00:11:24.080
but it leads to a failure to move forward.

00:11:24.080 --> 00:11:26.440
The Bible says in verse number four of Numbers 14,

00:11:26.440 --> 00:11:29.480
notice what it says, this congregation is speaking

00:11:29.480 --> 00:11:32.720
against the leadership and it says in verse number four,

00:11:32.720 --> 00:11:34.080
and they said one to another,

00:11:34.080 --> 00:11:39.080
let us make a captain and let us return into Egypt.

00:11:39.080 --> 00:11:40.240
And so what are they doing?

00:11:40.240 --> 00:11:41.920
Well, they're failing to move forward.

00:11:41.920 --> 00:11:45.200
Someone said this, we can't stay here and we can't go back

00:11:45.200 --> 00:11:47.680
so we must go forward.

00:11:47.680 --> 00:11:51.520
And the Christian life is a life that's based upon

00:11:51.640 --> 00:11:55.960
and really the impact or the opportunity to go forward,

00:11:55.960 --> 00:12:00.960
to press on, to claim what God has given us

00:12:01.500 --> 00:12:04.120
as the promises of his word and having faith

00:12:04.120 --> 00:12:05.440
and living by faith.

00:12:05.440 --> 00:12:09.480
We sing the wonderful hymn, onward, forward.

00:12:09.480 --> 00:12:12.520
We think about the truth of the Apostle Paul

00:12:12.520 --> 00:12:13.880
during the missionary journeys

00:12:13.880 --> 00:12:15.640
as we read of them in the book of Acts

00:12:15.640 --> 00:12:19.160
and man, they just were going forward with the gospel.

00:12:19.160 --> 00:12:20.920
Was it because everyone welcomed them

00:12:21.320 --> 00:12:22.480
and they rolled out the red carpet

00:12:22.480 --> 00:12:25.040
and said, we're so glad that you've come to our city?

00:12:25.040 --> 00:12:27.720
No, it's because they had faith.

00:12:28.560 --> 00:12:29.760
They were just believing God.

00:12:29.760 --> 00:12:33.680
God said in Acts chapter 13, separate unto me,

00:12:33.680 --> 00:12:35.760
Paul and Saul and Barnabas for the work

00:12:35.760 --> 00:12:37.680
whereunto I have called them.

00:12:37.680 --> 00:12:40.160
And we find that they were just operating

00:12:40.160 --> 00:12:43.180
based upon what God had revealed to them,

00:12:43.180 --> 00:12:46.020
living by faith and they were moving forward.

00:12:46.020 --> 00:12:49.160
And by the way, I'm thankful that they obeyed the Lord

00:12:49.160 --> 00:12:50.320
and they lived by faith.

00:12:50.320 --> 00:12:51.160
Why?

00:12:51.160 --> 00:12:53.640
Because the gospel went throughout the known world,

00:12:53.640 --> 00:12:56.480
eventually got to Europe, eventually got to America.

00:12:56.480 --> 00:12:59.240
If you kind of, I know that's a big couple of jumps,

00:12:59.240 --> 00:13:02.600
but historically, that's how it happened.

00:13:02.600 --> 00:13:04.960
Because some people that had some faith,

00:13:04.960 --> 00:13:06.600
they just believed God.

00:13:06.600 --> 00:13:08.680
They just said, I'm not concerned about all the obstacles.

00:13:08.680 --> 00:13:11.340
We know they're there, but we're gonna go forward.

00:13:11.340 --> 00:13:13.840
The children of Israel say, let us make a captain

00:13:13.840 --> 00:13:15.240
and let us return into Egypt.

00:13:15.240 --> 00:13:16.680
You know, oftentimes when we have doubt

00:13:16.680 --> 00:13:18.080
and unbelief in our lives,

00:13:18.080 --> 00:13:22.160
it causes us to lack real reason and logic.

00:13:23.160 --> 00:13:24.600
How are they gonna go back?

